about: Food and Product sales along street side on weekends ( Friday, Saturday and Sunday) from April 1st through November 1st every year. We will also specialize products from our local growers with an annual Scarecrow Festival during fall. We are expanding with our local FFA and tractor clubs. Bringing a lot of our community roots to the downtown area. There is so much to offer from our Fayette County farmers and local growers that we want to be able to share with those passing through along with working and blending with our Main Street Fayette Group and local monthly Shop Hops. Providing the needs of all people young and old with what nature has to offer and our individuals who want to share their product locally.

Open Saturdays, 9am to noon, April 28 - Nov 17, 2018. The mission of our non-profit, community-based market is to support excellent growers and producers while nurturing community appreciation of wholesome local foods in a lively neighborhood setting. We are a producer-only market, which means that everything you see at market is grown or produced by the stall farmer or cottage food producer.

about: The Frostville Museum Farmers' Market is located in the Rocky River Reservation, on the beautiful grounds of the Frostville Museum, a mid 1840's village. The village is open for tours May through October, during market hours. Each Saturday we have live music, children's activities and cooking demonstrations by local chefs and/or vendors. our kitchen is open for breakfast and lunch during the Market. We also host food trucks on the select Saturdays. Picnic tables and benches are located throughout the area. many special events and festivals are held at Frostville throughout the year. Please see our website for details. The market is handicap accessible.Outdoor market:May - October, every Saturday, 9am - 1pmIndoor market:November - April, every Saturday, 10am - 1pm in the Red Event Barn

about: June-October 1:00 PM - 4:00 PMThe mission of the Oak Hill Farmer’s Market is to provide an unique venue where local farmers, gourmet food producers, and artists can sell their high-quality products directly to the customer. The Market encourages direct communication between consumers and producers, fosters social gathering and community building and promotes nutritious food choices.  The Market seeks to educate the consumer about the many benefits to the individual, the community, and the environment of buying locally produced food, and to enhance and enrich the community of Richfield. Consumers can connect with a wide array of locally grown and produced foods and goods in a setting that allows them to interact directly with the grower or producer, thereby re-connecting them directly to the source.  The Market also provides and encourages local entrepreneurial opportunities and brings energy and excitement to Richfield Township. Oak Hill is dedicated to creating a space that allows for community interaction and enjoyment, informal public education, and civic engagement.
